The Telegraph - Calcutta

 Fleming to join squad today 

Sydney: New Zealand captain Stephen Fleming was on Friday cleared by doctors to join his teammates in Australia, team officials said. 

Fleming, who has been suffering from a virus contracted during New Zealand?s tour to Bangladesh last month, will arrive here on Saturday from New Zealand ahead of next week?s first of the two Test matches in Brisbane. 

Team officials said they expect the influential left-handed batsman to be fit for the first Test, starting on Thursday. (AFP) 

